          <p class="supertitle">Full Time / Hollywood, CA</p>
  <h1>Senior Systems Engineer / Backend Administrator (Ruby)</h1>

  <div class="columns generic ">
    <div class="column main">
      <p>We’re a small, focused startup about to come out of closed Beta making a killer desktop app for the music industry. Think Dropbox + Lightroom + YouSendIt.</p>

<p>We’re looking for a Ruby programmer with extensive Linux administration experience to take on the task of managing our backend systems. You’ll be working with a number of diverse backend services including MongoDB, Rails and Node.js, all running on Amazon EC2 servers.</p>

<p>You might be building automated systems to help with deployment, developing monitoring tools, or even figuring out ways to help with scalability.  We’re working at a breakneck pace adding cool new features and growing our userbase &ndash; so we’re looking for someone who can handle anything that’s thrown at them.  We’re still in beta, so you’ll be able to get in at the ground floor and have a real impact.</p>

<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Linux system administration and security</li>
<li>Great, in-depth knowledge of Ruby</li>
<li>Experience working with virtual hosting solutions like EC2/S3</li>
<li>Experience working with NoSQL database solutions</li>
<li>Extensive networking experience (configuration, debugging)</li>
</ul>


<p><strong>Pluses</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Good knowledge of scalability</li>
<li>Good knowledge of encryption</li>
<li>Experience building large sites with Amazon EC2/S3</li>
<li>Experience working with Javascript, Node.js</li>
<li>Knowledge of C++</li>
</ul>


<p><strong>Please don’t judge us by our placeholder website – it’s all programmer art! Our designers are almost done with a new version that won’t make your eyeballs bleed.</strong></p>
</div><!-- /.column.main -->

